items.name: Air Seal
items.itemInfo:
### Air Sealing
#### Why Clients Should Do This Service:
- Responsible for up to 50% of your home’s energy efficiency.
- Improves air quality by separating spaces that share 40%-60% of the air you breathe, if not properly air sealed.
- Extends and maximizes the lifespan of your HVAC system/s.
- #### When It Is Done:
- When air quality or energy efficiency concerns or issues arise.
- Only when the attic or crawl space is completely cleaned out and all insulation removed to expose areas in need of air sealing.
- After ducting installation, and before insulation installation. 
- #### How It Is Done:
- Identifying all gaps, cracks and crevices that may allow for air leakage between attic/crawl space and living space.
- Applying expanding foam to all electrical and plumbing protrusions, all HVAC boots and registers, and all non LED recessed lights to minimize air penetration. 
- By using specialized tools that allow technicians to reach the tightest and most difficult areas to ensure a comprehensive sealing throughout the entire space.

items.name: Gable Vents - Volcan
items.itemInfo:
Gable vents built to protect.
Gable vents are the vents on the exterior walls of a home’s attic to allow for proper airflow. In the summer, the home may be cooled with air conditioning but heat rises, getting caught under the roof. The same can be said of the winter, however, extreme temperature shifts are even harder on an attic’s open space. Gable vents provide necessary ventilation to deter condensation which can lead to mold and mildew.

The difference between gable vents and ridge vents and soffit vents (also exterior vents under the roof) is that gable vents are meant to show, adding an architectural element to the home. However, this doesn’t mean that the vent openings should stay vulnerable.

items.name: Gable Vents - Volcan
items.itemInfo:
Gable vents built to protect.
Gable vents are the vents on the exterior walls of a home’s attic to allow for proper airflow. In the summer, the home may be cooled with air conditioning but heat rises, getting caught under the roof. The same can be said of the winter, however, extreme temperature shifts are even harder on an attic’s open space. Gable vents provide necessary ventilation to deter condensation which can lead to mold and mildew.

The difference between gable vents and ridge vents and soffit vents (also exterior vents under the roof) is that gable vents are meant to show, adding an architectural element to the home. However, this doesn’t mean that the vent openings should stay vulnerable.

items.name: Gable Vents - Volcan
items.itemInfo:
Gable vents built to protect.
Gable vents are the vents on the exterior walls of a home’s attic to allow for proper airflow. In the summer, the home may be cooled with air conditioning but heat rises, getting caught under the roof. The same can be said of the winter, however, extreme temperature shifts are even harder on an attic’s open space. Gable vents provide necessary ventilation to deter condensation which can lead to mold and mildew.

The difference between gable vents and ridge vents and soffit vents (also exterior vents under the roof) is that gable vents are meant to show, adding an architectural element to the home. However, this doesn’t mean that the vent openings should stay vulnerable.

### Air Sealing
#### Why Clients Should Do This Service:
- Responsible for up to 50% of your home’s energy efficiency.
- Improves air quality by separating spaces that share 40%-60% of the air you breathe, if not properly air sealed.
- Extends and maximizes the lifespan of your HVAC system/s.
- #### When It Is Done:
- When air quality or energy efficiency concerns or issues arise.
- Only when the attic or crawl space is completely cleaned out and all insulation removed to expose areas in need of air sealing.
- After ducting installation, and before insulation installation. 
- #### How It Is Done:
- Identifying all gaps, cracks and crevices that may allow for air leakage between attic/crawl space and living space.
- Applying expanding foam to all electrical and plumbing protrusions, all HVAC boots and registers, and all non LED recessed lights to minimize air penetration. 
- By using specialized tools that allow technicians to reach the tightest and most difficult areas to ensure a comprehensive sealing throughout the entire space.

items.name: Gable Vents - Volcan
items.itemInfo:
Gable vents built to protect.
Gable vents are the vents on the exterior walls of a home’s attic to allow for proper airflow. In the summer, the home may be cooled with air conditioning but heat rises, getting caught under the roof. The same can be said of the winter, however, extreme temperature shifts are even harder on an attic’s open space. Gable vents provide necessary ventilation to deter condensation which can lead to mold and mildew.

The difference between gable vents and ridge vents and soffit vents (also exterior vents under the roof) is that gable vents are meant to show, adding an architectural element to the home. However, this doesn’t mean that the vent openings should stay vulnerable.
